A video of a driver crashing into an elderly woman carrying a child on her back has gone viral on social media. JOHANNESBURG - Police are investigating a case of reckless and negligent driving after a video of a driver crashing into an elderly woman carrying a child on her back gone viral on social media. The driver of the car, who appears to be a woman, allegedly switches seats with a man after the incident, they then drive off without helping the victim. Police say the two suspects were arrested after the owner of the vehicle handed himself to the police. The incident took place in Ventersburg in the Free State. The two suspects are out on bail and will appear in court on 30 January 2020. 